	   <tr><td colspan=2>Culled from tCH:<br><br>**** Spoiler Ahead *******<br><br>OK, fast heads up on what I've found so far. First, it seems the songs are quested. So, zone into the first zone and somewhere near the lighthouse in a hut is a NPC called Kardin Nillic (loc 1657, 48 ) . Follow his prompts (what plague, how are they immune, what singing or something like that) and he sends you off on a little quest.<br><br>Head south (I think its south) and you'll come across a beach, with a cave in it. Stick right and you'll come to a small troll town, and on the other side is a zone line to the next zone (yay!! educated guess to find it worked!!)<br><br>In this zone you'll need to head down to the docks where there is a tavern with a troubadour playing. I invised in, targetted him, stood outside and bellowed him. At 65 nothing else came. Straight toe to toe fight, he took about a bub off and I was too lazy to heal. Hit once for 94, and a couple of 55-60's but most were around 20. He dropped a coin and a book.<br><br>I gave book to Kardin who told me to toddle off and see Evanesque about it. Now I gotta find Evanesque. Coin did nothing, so I can only assume its for something else. Both coin and book were no drop btw.<br><br>Grunter Tonedeth<br>Maestro of Frayed Knot<br>The Rathe<br><br><br>the 'a Broken Skull troubadour' was light blue at 56.<br><br>Dropped 'a faded, watermarked book'.<br>When given to Kardin, he gives you 'a faded songbook'. <br>When given to Jusean, he gives you 'a transcribed songbook'.<br><br>Both items are magic/no drop, bard/all.<br><br>The song is itemized as 'Spell: Aria of Ascetism' and is no drop<br><br>Mileron<br><br><br>Jusean Evanesque is in the bard guild in Qeynos.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Feb 25 01:06:35 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Calliopeia Hearthorn<br>Virtuosa of the 60th Song<br>Still the Bardess<br>Mithaniel Marr<br><br>"I sing sometimes for the wars that I fight, 'cause every tool is a weapon if you hold it right."&nbsp;&nbsp;- Ani Difranco</td></tr>
